 the same from year to year...\nThat question did come up in the examination.", '试题;考题\n他从某处听说经济学考试的考题年年都一样。\n那道题确实在考试中出现了。'], ["CONVENTION\nIf you say 'Good question' in reply to a question, you mean that it is a difficult question to answer, or perhaps that you are embarrassed about the answer or do not know the answer.", "问得好，问得真有水平(用于问题难以回答、不便回答或不知道答案时)\n'Why didn't you appoint Ron twelve months ago?'—'Good question.'\n“你为什么12个月前不任命罗恩呢？”——“问得好。”"], ["PHRASE\nThe person, thing, or time in question is one which you have just been talking about or which is relevant.\nThe player in question is Mark Williams...\nAdd up all the income you've received over the period in question.", '被提及的;讨论中的;相关的\n我们所说的那个选手是马克·威廉斯。\n把那个时期里你拿到的所有收入加在一起。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you say that something is out of the question, you are emphasizing that it is completely impossible or unacceptable.\nFor the homeless, private medical care is simply out of the question...\nIs a tax increase still out of the question?', '不可能;办不到;无法接受\n对于无家可归的人而言，私人医疗纯粹是天方夜谭。\n增加税收仍然是不可能的事吗？'], ['PHRASE\nIf you pop the question, you ask someone to marry you.\nStuart got serious quickly and popped the question six months later.', '求婚\n斯图尔特很快认真起来，6个月之后便求婚了。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you say there is no question of something happening, you are emphasizing that it is not going to happen.\nAs far as he was concerned there was no question of betraying his own comrades...\nThere is no question of the taxpayer picking up the bill for the party.', '（表示强调）是不可能的\n就他而言，背叛自己的同志是不可能的。\n要纳税人为该党买单是不可能的。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you do something without question, you do it without arguing or asking why it is necessary.\n...military formations, carrying out without question the battle orders of superior officers.', '毫无疑问地;毫无异议地\n毫无异议地执行上级军官的战斗命令的部队编队'], ['PHRASE\nYou use without question to emphasize the opinion you are expressing.\nHe was our greatest storyteller, without question.', '毫无疑问(表示强调自己的观点)\n毫无疑问，他是我们最会讲故事的人。']]}]